<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06271134 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06271134 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SPORTS; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Thomas Weisel, an official with the U.S. Ski Association, describes GeorgeSteinbrenner, a U.S. Olympic Committee vice president, as a &quot;bumbling idiot&quot;and &quot;a disgrace to sport&quot; in the current issue of &quot;Ski Racing International.&quot;;  Weisel further criticized the USOC and Steinbrenner by alluding to his pastproblems in baseball as the owner of the New York Yankees, saying, &quot;The factthey've got a person like Steinbrenner in a visible position is a testament tothe problems they have.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  U.S. SKI OFFICIAL CALLS STEINBRENNER 'BUMBLINGIDIOT'  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Sports Digest  </MEMO><TEXT>     Steinbrenner said, &quot;It doesn't bother me at all; I've been called worsethings.&quot;; FOOTBALL: Pro Bowl nose tackle Erik Howard of the New York Giants istentatively scheduled to undergo surgery today on a herniated disk. The formerBellarmine Prep player will be out at least four weeks and perhaps the rest ofthe season. The Giants signed veteran nose tackle Greg Meisner to bolstertheir line.; BOXING: Bantamweight Fernie Morales, who underwent emergencybrain surgery Saturday after a fight, tested positive for alcohol and mighthave been legally drunk during the bout, the Los Angeles Times reported. . . .Riddick Bowe, just elevated to the No. 2 heavyweight contender's ranking bythe World Boxing Council, is not signed to fight Donovan Ruddock, according toBowe's manager, contradicting published reports that the bout was set.;MISCELLANY: Nancy Scranton, Dottie Mochrie and Deedee Lasker shot 4-under-par68s to share the lead in the rain-shortened opening round of a $350,000 LPGAtournament. . . . The Davis Cup final between France and the United Stateswill be played in a Lyon, France, arena starting Nov. 29. The type of surfacewas not announced but is expected to be a fast, synthetic variety.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910927  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  12D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  285  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, September 27, 199100271134,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>